    "title": "[DSP-7955 1/2] Implement DAG cycle detection/resolution, additional context for error messages",
    "description": "There are a few other miscellaneous small fixes here:\n\n* prevent timeouts/failed jobs from showing PASSED status\n* add failure reason metadata to dynamodb events table to pass that context back to the cli\n\nExample new notifications:\n\nmultiple cycles:\n\n![Screenshot 2026-04-02 at 11.18.31\u202fAM.png](/uploads/a67bff4d147a36b9377951a2711857ad/Screenshot_2026-04-02_at_11.18.31_AM.png){width=620 height=101}\n\nsingle cycle:\n\n![Screenshot 2026-04-02 at 11.17.34\u202fAM.png](/uploads/266bc1bf6df3ea89863a5bdf0ac7e8fd/Screenshot_2026-04-02_at_11.17.34_AM.png){width=467 height=83}\n\nDAG registration failure (rare, but could be caused by any number of reasons)\n\n![Screenshot 2026-04-02 at 11.18.09\u202fAM.png](/uploads/03178871eaa5c28d8d8bd38b9f3d4bbb/Screenshot_2026-04-02_at_11.18.09_AM.png){width=468 height=57}\n\nCloses DSP-7955",
