  {
    "id": 470129119,
    "iid": 92,
    "project_id": 46011246,
    "title": "[DSP-7955 1/2] Implement cycle detection/resolution",
    "description": "The following MR implements cycle detection via a Depth-First Search, recursively traversing the dependency graph until it detects that the next node would add a dependency that is already in the `IN_STACK` list, meaning that the DAG is no longer acyclic. When this occurs, a Slack/CLI notification is posted:\n\n![image.png](/uploads/ccfec439b8f1fa4dfd163de809d3e82a/image.png){width=900 height=147}\n\nThis MR also implements an optional parameter, `fix_dag_cycle`, which is used when a cycle already exists in dynamo. In this case, even if the luna-dependencies.yaml has been updated, dynamodb can't be updated until seiji deploys. If Airflow can't deploy due to the cycle, there's no way to fix it in dynamo; thus: `fix_dag_cycle` allows Airflow to temporarily pop the cycled dependencies off of the DAG\n\nCloses DSP-7955",
    "state": "opened",
    "created_at": "2026-04-02T19:05:11.006Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-03T17:53:01.316Z",
